{{Gnosticism}}
'''Sarkic''', from the Greek ''σάρξ'', flesh (or '''hylic''', from the Greek ''ὕλη'', stuff, or matter) in [[gnosticism]] describes the lowest level of [[human nature]]&nbsp;— the fleshly, instinctive level.  This isn't the notion of body as opposed to thought; rather the sarkic level is said to be the lowest level of thought.

